<h1>Xiangxin Zhu</h1> 
<p style="font-size:14px"><em>(Xiangxin is pronounced "Shee-ah-ng Shee-n", and Zhu is pronounced "Drew")</em></p>

<p>I am a computer science Ph.D. student at <a href="http://www.uci.edu">UC Irvine</a>. I work at <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu">School of Information and Computer Sciences</a> with the <a href="http://vision.ics.uci.edu">Computational Vision Group</a> where I am advised by <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~dramanan">Professor Deva Ramanan</a> and <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~welling">Professor Max Welling</a>. I am broadly interested in computer vision, machine learning and their applications.</p>

<!--<p>Recent projects I've worked on:</p>-->
<!--<ul>-->
    <!--<li> Face analysis, including detection, pose estimation and landmark estimation.-->
    <!--<li> Object detection with large training data.-->
    <!--<li> Predicting simulation parameters of biological systems using Gaussian process regression.-->
<!--</ul>-->

<p>The best way to reach me is through email:</p>	
<ul>
<!--<li>Email: <a href="mailto:xzhu@ics.uci.edu">xzhu@ics.uci.edu</a></li>-->
<li>Email: xzhu (at) ics.uci.edu</li>
<li>Office: 4209 Donald Bren Hall</li>
</ul>

<p>Previously, I completed my M.E. in <a
href="http://english.ia.cas.cn/">Institute of Automation</a>, <a
href="http://english.cas.cn/">Chinese Academy of Sciences</a> with <a
href="http://www.cbsr.ia.ac.cn/users/szli/">Professor Stan Li</a>, and B.S. in
<a href="http://www.tsinghua.edu.cn/publish/then/index.html">Tsinghua
University</a>, Beijing, China. I was at <a
href="http://www.google.com/mobile/goggles/">Google Visual Search</a> for the summer of
2012 working with <a href="http://ai.stanford.edu/~drago/">Drago Anguelov</a>.

